==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Singer
<hw>Sin"ger</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧n"j⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Singe</er>.]</ety> <def>One who, or that which, singes.</def>
<specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One employed to singe
cloth.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A machine for singeing cloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Singer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Singer
<hw>Sing"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Sing</er>.]</ety> <def>One who sings; especially, one whose
profession is to sing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Singeress</ent>⟦br⟧
